{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When I got my current job, I was given a good piece of advice,"},{"time":3000,"text":"which was to interview three politicians every day."},{"time":6000,"text":"And from that much contact with politicians,"},{"time":8000,"text":"I can tell you they're all emotional freaks of one sort or another."},{"time":12000,"text":"They have what I called \"logorrhea dementia,\""},{"time":14000,"text":"which is they talk so much they drive themselves insane."},{"time":17000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":19000,"text":"But what they do have is incredible social skills."},{"time":22000,"text":"When you meet them, they lock into you,"},{"time":24000,"text":"they look you in the eye,"},{"time":26000,"text":"they invade your personal space,"},{"time":28000,"text":"they massage the back of your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"I had dinner with a Republican senator several months ago"},{"time":32000,"text":"who kept his hand on my inner thigh"},{"time":34000,"text":"throughout the whole meal -- squeezing it."},{"time":37000,"text":"I once -- this was years ago --"},{"time":39000,"text":"I saw Ted Kennedy and Dan Quayle meet in the well of the Senate."},{"time":41000,"text":"And they were friends, and they hugged each other"},{"time":43000,"text":"and they were laughing, and their faces were like this far apart."},{"time":46000,"text":"And they were moving and grinding"},{"time":48000,"text":"and moving their arms up and down each other."},{"time":50000,"text":"And I was like, \"Get a room. I don't want to see this.\""},{"time":53000,"text":"But they have those social skills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"Another case:"},{"time":57000,"text":"Last election cycle,"},{"time":59000,"text":"I was following Mitt Romney around New Hampshire,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and he was campaigning with his five perfect sons:"},{"time":64000,"text":"Bip, Chip, Rip, Zip, Lip and Dip."},{"time":66000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":68000,"text":"And he's going into a diner."},{"time":70000,"text":"And he goes into the diner, introduces himself to a family"},{"time":73000,"text":"and says, \"What village are you from in New Hampshire?\""},{"time":75000,"text":"And then he describes the home he owned in their village."},{"time":79000,"text":"And so he goes around the room,"},{"time":82000,"text":"and then as he's leaving the diner,"},{"time":84000,"text":"he first-names almost everybody he's just met."},{"time":87000,"text":"I was like, \"Okay, that's social skill.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":89000,"text":"But the paradox is,"},{"time":91000,"text":"when a lot of these people slip into the policy-making mode,"},{"time":95000,"text":"that social awareness vanishes"},{"time":97000,"text":"and they start talking like accountants."},{"time":99000,"text":"So in the course of my career,"},{"time":101000,"text":"I have covered a series of failures."},{"time":103000,"text":"We sent economists in the Soviet Union"},{"time":105000,"text":"with privatization plans when it broke up,"},{"time":107000,"text":"and what they really lacked was social trust."},{"time":110000,"text":"We invaded Iraq with a military"},{"time":112000,"text":"oblivious to the cultural and psychological realities."},{"time":115000,"text":"We had a financial regulatory regime"},{"time":117000,"text":"based on the assumptions"},{"time":119000,"text":"that traders were rational creatures"},{"time":121000,"text":"who wouldn't do anything stupid."},{"time":123000,"text":"For 30 years, I've been covering school reform"},{"time":126000,"text":"and we've basically reorganized the bureaucratic boxes --"},{"time":129000,"text":"charters, private schools, vouchers --"},{"time":132000,"text":"but we've had disappointing results year after year."},{"time":136000,"text":"And the fact is, people learn from people they love."},{"time":139000,"text":"And if you're not talking about the individual relationship"},{"time":141000,"text":"between a teacher and a student,"},{"time":143000,"text":"you're not talking about that reality."},{"time":145000,"text":"But that reality is expunged"},{"time":147000,"text":"from our policy-making process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"And so that's led to a question for me:"},{"time":152000,"text":"Why are the most socially-attuned people on earth"},{"time":155000,"text":"completely dehumanized"},{"time":157000,"text":"when they think about policy?"},{"time":160000,"text":"And I came to the conclusion,"},{"time":162000,"text":"this is a symptom of a larger problem."},{"time":165000,"text":"That, for centuries, we've inherited a view of human nature"},{"time":168000,"text":"based on the notion"},{"time":170000,"text":"that we're divided selves,"},{"time":172000,"text":"that reason is separated from the emotions"},{"time":175000,"text":"and that society progresses"},{"time":177000,"text":"to the extent that reason can suppress the passions."},{"time":180000,"text":"And it's led to a view of human nature"},{"time":183000,"text":"that we're rational individuals"},{"time":185000,"text":"who respond in straightforward ways to incentives,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and it's led to ways of seeing the world"},{"time":191000,"text":"where people try to use the assumptions of physics"},{"time":194000,"text":"to measure how human behavior is."},{"time":199000,"text":"And it's produced a great amputation,"},{"time":201000,"text":"a shallow view of human nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"We're really good at talking about material things,"},{"time":206000,"text":"but we're really bad at talking about emotions."},{"time":209000,"text":"We're really good at talking about skills"},{"time":211000,"text":"and safety and health;"},{"time":213000,"text":"we're really bad at talking about character."},{"time":216000,"text":"Alasdair MacIntyre, the famous philosopher,"},{"time":219000,"text":"said that, \"We have the concepts of the ancient morality"},{"time":222000,"text":"of virtue, honor, goodness,"},{"time":224000,"text":"but we no longer have a system"},{"time":226000,"text":"by which to connect them.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"And so this has led to a shallow path in politics,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but also in a whole range of human endeavors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":235000,"text":"You can see it in the way we raise our young kids."},{"time":238000,"text":"You go to an elementary school at three in the afternoon"},{"time":241000,"text":"and you watch the kids come out,"},{"time":243000,"text":"and they're wearing these 80-pound backpacks."},{"time":246000,"text":"If the wind blows them over, they're like beetles stuck there on the ground."},{"time":250000,"text":"You see these cars that drive up --"},{"time":252000,"text":"usually it's Saabs and Audis and Volvos,"},{"time":255000,"text":"because in certain neighborhoods it's socially acceptable to have a luxury car,"},{"time":258000,"text":"so long as it comes from a country hostile to U.S. foreign policy --"},{"time":261000,"text":"that's fine."},{"time":263000,"text":"They get picked up by these creatures I've called uber-moms,"},{"time":266000,"text":"who are highly successful career women"},{"time":268000,"text":"who have taken time off to make sure all their kids get into Harvard."},{"time":271000,"text":"And you can usually tell the uber-moms"},{"time":273000,"text":"because they actually weigh less than their own children."},{"time":275000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":277000,"text":"So at the moment of conception,"},{"time":279000,"text":"they're doing little butt exercises."},{"time":281000,"text":"Babies flop out,"},{"time":283000,"text":"they're flashing Mandarin flashcards at the things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286000,"text":"Driving them home, and they want them to be enlightened,"},{"time":289000,"text":"so they take them to Ben &amp; Jerry's ice cream company"},{"time":291000,"text":"with its own foreign policy."},{"time":293000,"text":"In one of my books,"},{"time":295000,"text":"I joke that Ben &amp; Jerry's should make a pacifist toothpaste --"},{"time":297000,"text":"doesn't kill germs, just asks them to leave."},{"time":299000,"text":"It would be a big seller."},{"time":301000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":303000,"text":"And they go to Whole Foods to get their baby formula,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and Whole Foods is one of those progressive grocery stores"},{"time":308000,"text":"where all the cashiers look like they're on loan from Amnesty International."},{"time":311000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":313000,"text":"They buy these seaweed-based snacks there"},{"time":315000,"text":"called Veggie Booty with Kale,"},{"time":317000,"text":"which is for kids who come home and say,"},{"time":319000,"text":"\"Mom, mom, I want a snack that'll help prevent colon-rectal cancer.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324000,"text":"And so the kids are raised in a certain way,"},{"time":326000,"text":"jumping through achievement hoops of the things we can measure --"},{"time":329000,"text":"SAT prep, oboe, soccer practice."},{"time":332000,"text":"They get into competitive colleges, they get good jobs,"},{"time":335000,"text":"and sometimes they make a success of themselves"},{"time":337000,"text":"in a superficial manner, and they make a ton of money."},{"time":340000,"text":"And sometimes you can see them at vacation places"},{"time":342000,"text":"like Jackson Hole or Aspen."},{"time":344000,"text":"And they've become elegant and slender --"},{"time":346000,"text":"they don't really have thighs;"},{"time":348000,"text":"they just have one elegant calve on top of another."},{"time":351000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":353000,"text":"They have kids of their own,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and they've achieved a genetic miracle by marrying beautiful people,"},{"time":358000,"text":"so their grandmoms look like Gertrude Stein,"},{"time":361000,"text":"their daughters looks like Halle Berry -- I don't know how they've done that."},{"time":364000,"text":"They get there and they realize"},{"time":367000,"text":"it's fashionable now to have dogs a third as tall as your ceiling heights."},{"time":371000,"text":"So they've got these furry 160-pound dogs --"},{"time":374000,"text":"all look like velociraptors,"},{"time":377000,"text":"all named after Jane Austen characters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380000,"text":"And then when they get old, they haven't really developed a philosophy of life,"},{"time":383000,"text":"but they've decided, \"I've been successful at everything;"},{"time":385000,"text":"I'm just not going to die.\""},{"time":387000,"text":"And so they hire personal trainers;"},{"time":390000,"text":"they're popping Cialis like breath mints."},{"time":392000,"text":"You see them on the mountains up there."},{"time":394000,"text":"They're cross-country skiing up the mountain"},{"time":396000,"text":"with these grim expressions"},{"time":398000,"text":"that make Dick Cheney look like Jerry Lewis."},{"time":400000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":402000,"text":"And as they whiz by you,"},{"time":404000,"text":"it's like being passed by a little iron Raisinet"},{"time":406000,"text":"going up the hill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"And so this is part of what life is,"},{"time":413000,"text":"but it's not all of what life is."},{"time":416000,"text":"And over the past few years,"},{"time":418000,"text":"I think we've been given a deeper view of human nature"},{"time":422000,"text":"and a deeper view of who we are."},{"time":424000,"text":"And it's not based on theology or philosophy,"},{"time":426000,"text":"it's in the study of the mind,"},{"time":428000,"text":"across all these spheres of research,"},{"time":430000,"text":"from neuroscience to the cognitive scientists,"},{"time":432000,"text":"behavioral economists, psychologists,"},{"time":434000,"text":"sociology,"},{"time":436000,"text":"we're developing a revolution in consciousness."},{"time":439000,"text":"And when you synthesize it all,"},{"time":441000,"text":"it's giving us a new view of human nature."},{"time":443000,"text":"And far from being a coldly materialistic view of nature,"},{"time":446000,"text":"it's a new humanism, it's a new enchantment."},{"time":449000,"text":"And I think when you synthesize this research,"},{"time":451000,"text":"you start with three key insights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":453000,"text":"The first insight is"},{"time":455000,"text":"that while the conscious mind writes the autobiography of our species,"},{"time":458000,"text":"the unconscious mind does most of the work."},{"time":462000,"text":"And so one way to formulate that is"},{"time":464000,"text":"the human mind can take in millions of pieces of information a minute,"},{"time":467000,"text":"of which it can be consciously aware of about 40."},{"time":470000,"text":"And this leads to oddities."},{"time":472000,"text":"One of my favorite is that people named Dennis"},{"time":474000,"text":"are disproportionately likely to become dentists,"},{"time":477000,"text":"people named Lawrence become lawyers,"},{"time":479000,"text":"because unconsciously we gravitate toward things"},{"time":481000,"text":"that sound familiar,"},{"time":483000,"text":"which is why I named my daughter President of the United States Brooks."},{"time":486000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":489000,"text":"Another finding is that the unconscious,"},{"time":492000,"text":"far from being dumb and sexualized,"},{"time":494000,"text":"is actually quite smart."},{"time":496000,"text":"So one of the most cognitively demanding things we do is buy furniture."},{"time":499000,"text":"It's really hard to imagine a sofa, how it's going to look in your house."},{"time":502000,"text":"And the way you should do that"},{"time":504000,"text":"is study the furniture,"},{"time":506000,"text":"let it marinate in your mind, distract yourself,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and then a few days later, go with your gut,"},{"time":510000,"text":"because unconsciously you've figured it out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512000,"text":"The second insight"},{"time":514000,"text":"is that emotions are at the center of our thinking."},{"time":517000,"text":"People with strokes and lesions"},{"time":519000,"text":"in the emotion-processing parts of the brain"},{"time":521000,"text":"are not super smart,"},{"time":523000,"text":"they're actually sometimes quite helpless."},{"time":525000,"text":"And the \"giant\" in the field is in the room tonight"},{"time":527000,"text":"and is speaking tomorrow morning -- Antonio Damasio."},{"time":530000,"text":"And one of the things he's really shown us"},{"time":532000,"text":"is that emotions are not separate from reason,"},{"time":535000,"text":"but they are the foundation of reason"},{"time":537000,"text":"because they tell us what to value."},{"time":539000,"text":"And so reading and educating your emotions"},{"time":541000,"text":"is one of the central activities of wisdom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544000,"text":"Now I'm a middle-aged guy."},{"time":546000,"text":"I'm not exactly comfortable with emotions."},{"time":548000,"text":"One of my favorite brain stories described these middle-aged guys."},{"time":551000,"text":"They put them into a brain scan machine --"},{"time":554000,"text":"this is apocryphal by the way, but I don't care --"},{"time":557000,"text":"and they had them watch a horror movie,"},{"time":560000,"text":"and then they had them describe their feelings toward their wives."},{"time":564000,"text":"And the brain scans were identical in both activities."},{"time":567000,"text":"It was just sheer terror."},{"time":569000,"text":"So me talking about emotion"},{"time":571000,"text":"is like Gandhi talking about gluttony,"},{"time":573000,"text":"but it is the central organizing process"},{"time":575000,"text":"of the way we think."},{"time":577000,"text":"It tells us what to imprint."},{"time":579000,"text":"The brain is the record of the feelings of a life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"And the third insight"},{"time":583000,"text":"is that we're not primarily self-contained individuals."},{"time":587000,"text":"We're social animals, not rational animals."},{"time":590000,"text":"We emerge out of relationships,"},{"time":592000,"text":"and we are deeply interpenetrated, one with another."},{"time":595000,"text":"And so when we see another person,"},{"time":597000,"text":"we reenact in our own minds"},{"time":599000,"text":"what we see in their minds."},{"time":601000,"text":"When we watch a car chase in a movie,"},{"time":603000,"text":"it's almost as if we are subtly having a car chase."},{"time":606000,"text":"When we watch pornography,"},{"time":608000,"text":"it's a little like having sex,"},{"time":610000,"text":"though probably not as good."},{"time":612000,"text":"And we see this when lovers walk down the street,"},{"time":615000,"text":"when a crowd in Egypt or Tunisia"},{"time":617000,"text":"gets caught up in an emotional contagion,"},{"time":619000,"text":"the deep interpenetration."},{"time":621000,"text":"And this revolution in who we are"},{"time":624000,"text":"gives us a different way of seeing, I think, politics,"},{"time":627000,"text":"a different way, most importantly,"},{"time":629000,"text":"of seeing human capital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631000,"text":"We are now children of the French Enlightenment."},{"time":635000,"text":"We believe that reason is the highest of the faculties."},{"time":638000,"text":"But I think this research shows"},{"time":640000,"text":"that the British Enlightenment, or the Scottish Enlightenment,"},{"time":642000,"text":"with David Hume, Adam Smith,"},{"time":644000,"text":"actually had a better handle on who we are --"},{"time":647000,"text":"that reason is often weak, our sentiments are strong,"},{"time":650000,"text":"and our sentiments are often trustworthy."},{"time":653000,"text":"And this work corrects that bias in our culture,"},{"time":656000,"text":"that dehumanizing bias."},{"time":658000,"text":"It gives us a deeper sense"},{"time":660000,"text":"of what it actually takes"},{"time":662000,"text":"for us to thrive in this life."},{"time":664000,"text":"When we think about human capital"},{"time":666000,"text":"we think about the things we can measure easily --"},{"time":669000,"text":"things like grades, SAT's, degrees,"},{"time":672000,"text":"the number of years in schooling."},{"time":674000,"text":"What it really takes to do well, to lead a meaningful life,"},{"time":677000,"text":"are things that are deeper,"},{"time":679000,"text":"things we don't really even have words for."},{"time":682000,"text":"And so let me list just a couple of the things"},{"time":684000,"text":"I think this research points us toward trying to understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688000,"text":"The first gift, or talent, is mindsight --"},{"time":691000,"text":"the ability to enter into other people's minds"},{"time":695000,"text":"and learn what they have to offer."},{"time":697000,"text":"Babies come with this ability."},{"time":699000,"text":"Meltzoff, who's at the University of Washington,"},{"time":701000,"text":"leaned over a baby who was 43 minutes old."},{"time":704000,"text":"He wagged his tongue at the baby."},{"time":706000,"text":"The baby wagged her tongue back."},{"time":709000,"text":"Babies are born to interpenetrate into Mom's mind"},{"time":712000,"text":"and to download what they find --"},{"time":714000,"text":"their models of how to understand reality."},{"time":716000,"text":"In the United States, 55 percent of babies"},{"time":719000,"text":"have a deep two-way conversation with Mom"},{"time":721000,"text":"and they learn models to how to relate to other people."},{"time":724000,"text":"And those people who have models of how to relate"},{"time":726000,"text":"have a huge head start in life."},{"time":728000,"text":"Scientists at the University of Minnesota did a study"},{"time":730000,"text":"in which they could predict"},{"time":732000,"text":"with 77 percent accuracy, at age 18 months,"},{"time":735000,"text":"who was going to graduate from high school,"},{"time":737000,"text":"based on who had good attachment with mom."},{"time":740000,"text":"Twenty percent of kids do not have those relationships."},{"time":743000,"text":"They are what we call avoidantly attached."},{"time":745000,"text":"They have trouble relating to other people."},{"time":747000,"text":"They go through life"},{"time":749000,"text":"like sailboats tacking into the wind --"},{"time":751000,"text":"wanting to get close to people,"},{"time":753000,"text":"but not really having the models of how to do that."},{"time":756000,"text":"And so this is one skill"},{"time":758000,"text":"of how to hoover up knowledge, one from another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"A second skill is equipoise,"},{"time":763000,"text":"the ability to have the serenity"},{"time":765000,"text":"to read the biases and failures in your own mind."},{"time":768000,"text":"So for example, we are overconfidence machines."},{"time":771000,"text":"Ninety-five percent of our professors report"},{"time":774000,"text":"that they are above-average teachers."},{"time":776000,"text":"Ninety-six percent of college students"},{"time":778000,"text":"say they have above-average social skills."},{"time":781000,"text":"Time magazine asked Americans, \"Are you in the top one percent of earners?\""},{"time":784000,"text":"Nineteen percent of Americans are in the top one percent of earners."},{"time":787000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":789000,"text":"This is a gender-linked trait, by the way."},{"time":791000,"text":"Men drown at twice the rate of women,"},{"time":793000,"text":"because men think they can swim across that lake."},{"time":796000,"text":"But some people have the ability and awareness"},{"time":799000,"text":"of their own biases, their own overconfidence."},{"time":802000,"text":"They have epistemological modesty."},{"time":804000,"text":"They are open-minded in the face of ambiguity."},{"time":807000,"text":"They are able to adjust strength of the conclusions"},{"time":809000,"text":"to the strength of their evidence."},{"time":811000,"text":"They are curious."},{"time":813000,"text":"And these traits are often unrelated and uncorrelated with IQ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"The third trait is metis,"},{"time":818000,"text":"what we might call street smarts -- it's a Greek word."},{"time":821000,"text":"It's a sensitivity to the physical environment,"},{"time":823000,"text":"the ability to pick out patterns in an environment --"},{"time":825000,"text":"derive a gist."},{"time":827000,"text":"One of my colleagues at the Times"},{"time":829000,"text":"did a great story about soldiers in Iraq"},{"time":831000,"text":"who could look down a street and detect somehow"},{"time":834000,"text":"whether there was an IED, a landmine, in the street."},{"time":836000,"text":"They couldn't tell you how they did it,"},{"time":838000,"text":"but they could feel cold, they felt a coldness,"},{"time":841000,"text":"and they were more often right than wrong."},{"time":844000,"text":"The third is what you might call sympathy,"},{"time":846000,"text":"the ability to work within groups."},{"time":849000,"text":"And that comes in tremendously handy,"},{"time":852000,"text":"because groups are smarter than individuals."},{"time":854000,"text":"And face-to-face groups are much smarter"},{"time":856000,"text":"than groups that communicate electronically,"},{"time":859000,"text":"because 90 percent of our communication is non-verbal."},{"time":862000,"text":"And the effectiveness of a group"},{"time":864000,"text":"is not determined by the IQ of the group;"},{"time":867000,"text":"it's determined by how well they communicate,"},{"time":870000,"text":"how often they take turns in conversation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873000,"text":"Then you could talk about a trait like blending."},{"time":876000,"text":"Any child can say, \"I'm a tiger,\" pretend to be a tiger."},{"time":879000,"text":"It seems so elementary."},{"time":881000,"text":"But in fact, it's phenomenally complicated"},{"time":883000,"text":"to take a concept \"I\" and a concept \"tiger\""},{"time":885000,"text":"and blend them together."},{"time":887000,"text":"But this is the source of innovation."},{"time":889000,"text":"What Picasso did, for example,"},{"time":891000,"text":"was take the concept \"Western art\""},{"time":893000,"text":"and the concept \"African masks\""},{"time":895000,"text":"and blend them together --"},{"time":897000,"text":"not only the geometry,"},{"time":899000,"text":"but the moral systems entailed in them."},{"time":901000,"text":"And these are skills, again, we can't count and measure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903000,"text":"And then the final thing I'll mention"},{"time":905000,"text":"is something you might call limerence."},{"time":907000,"text":"And this is not an ability;"},{"time":909000,"text":"it's a drive and a motivation."},{"time":912000,"text":"The conscious mind hungers for success and prestige."},{"time":915000,"text":"The unconscious mind hungers"},{"time":917000,"text":"for those moments of transcendence,"},{"time":919000,"text":"when the skull line disappears"},{"time":921000,"text":"and we are lost in a challenge or a task --"},{"time":924000,"text":"when a craftsman feels lost in his craft,"},{"time":927000,"text":"when a naturalist feels at one with nature,"},{"time":930000,"text":"when a believer feels at one with God's love."},{"time":933000,"text":"That is what the unconscious mind hungers for."},{"time":936000,"text":"And many of us feel it in love"},{"time":938000,"text":"when lovers feel fused."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"And one of the most beautiful descriptions"},{"time":942000,"text":"I've come across in this research"},{"time":945000,"text":"of how minds interpenetrate"},{"time":947000,"text":"was written by a great theorist and scientist"},{"time":949000,"text":"named Douglas Hofstadter at the University of Indiana."},{"time":952000,"text":"He was married to a woman named Carol,"},{"time":954000,"text":"and they had a wonderful relationship."},{"time":956000,"text":"When their kids were five and two,"},{"time":958000,"text":"Carol had a stroke and a brain tumor and died suddenly."},{"time":962000,"text":"And Hofstadter wrote a book"},{"time":964000,"text":"called \"I Am a Strange Loop.\""},{"time":966000,"text":"In the course of that book, he describes a moment --"},{"time":968000,"text":"just months after Carol has died --"},{"time":971000,"text":"he comes across her picture on the mantel,"},{"time":973000,"text":"or on a bureau in his bedroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"And here's what he wrote:"},{"time":977000,"text":"\"I looked at her face,"},{"time":979000,"text":"and I looked so deeply"},{"time":981000,"text":"that I felt I was behind her eyes."},{"time":983000,"text":"And all at once I found myself saying"},{"time":985000,"text":"as tears flowed,"},{"time":987000,"text":"'That's me. That's me.'"},{"time":989000,"text":"And those simple words"},{"time":991000,"text":"brought back many thoughts that I had had before,"},{"time":993000,"text":"about the fusion of our souls"},{"time":995000,"text":"into one higher-level entity,"},{"time":997000,"text":"about the fact that at the core of both our souls"},{"time":1000000,"text":"lay our identical hopes and dreams for our children,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"about the notion that those hopes"},{"time":1006000,"text":"were not separate or distinct hopes,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"but were just one hope,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"one clear thing that defined us both,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"that welded us into a unit --"},{"time":1014000,"text":"the kind of unit I had but dimly imagined"},{"time":1017000,"text":"before being married and having children."},{"time":1020000,"text":"I realized that, though Carol had died,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"that core piece of her had not died at all,"},{"time":1025000,"text":"but had lived on very determinedly in my brain.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"The Greeks say we suffer our way to wisdom."},{"time":1032000,"text":"Through his suffering, Hofstadter understood"},{"time":1034000,"text":"how deeply interpenetrated we are."},{"time":1037000,"text":"Through the policy failures of the last 30 years,"},{"time":1040000,"text":"we have come to acknowledge, I think,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"how shallow our view of human nature has been."},{"time":1046000,"text":"And now as we confront that shallowness"},{"time":1049000,"text":"and the failures that derive from our inability"},{"time":1051000,"text":"to get the depths of who we are,"},{"time":1053000,"text":"comes this revolution in consciousness --"},{"time":1055000,"text":"these people in so many fields"},{"time":1058000,"text":"exploring the depth of our nature"},{"time":1060000,"text":"and coming away with this enchanted,"},{"time":1062000,"text":"this new humanism."},{"time":1064000,"text":"And when Freud discovered his sense of the unconscious,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"it had a vast effect on the climate of the times."},{"time":1069000,"text":"Now we are discovering a more accurate vision"},{"time":1072000,"text":"of the unconscious, of who we are deep inside,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"and it's going to have a wonderful and profound"},{"time":1077000,"text":"and humanizing effect on our culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}